        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Too Long; Didn't Read Act of 2019 or the TL; DR Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill requires a federal agency to provide a clearly-marked section at the top of a communication (both hard copy and electronic) that the agency sends to an individual if such communication requires or authorizes such individual to act.</p> <p>The clearly-marked section shall include</p> <ul> <li> the authorized or required action; </li> <li> if a response by the individual is required, optional, or not permitted; </li> <li> all deadlines to complete the authorized or required action; </li> <li> how to complete the authorized or required action; and </li> <li> the contact information for the agency, department, or office that can assist or answer questions relating to the authorized or required action. </li></ul>]]></text>
      </summary>
